'''Kim Tae-hyeon''' ({{Korean|hangul=김태현}}; born 17 September 2000) is a South Korean [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a left-footed [[centre-back]] for {{Japanese football updater|KashimaA}} club [[Kashima Antlers]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=J.LEAGUE Data Site |url=https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX04/?player_id=45209}}</ref> and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

==Career==

On 28 December 2021, Kim joined Vegalta Sendai on a one year loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegalta.co.jp/backnumber/2021/news-team/2021/12/post-1018.html|title=蔚山現代FC キム テヒョン選手 期限付き移籍加入内定のお知らせ|trans-title=Ulsan Hyundai FC announces that Kim Tae-hyun will join the team on a temporary transfer|language=Japanese|website=www.vegalta.co.jp}}</ref>

On 10 January 2024, Kim joined Sagan Tosu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/27493/|title=キム テヒョン選手 完全移籍加入のお知らせ|trans-title=Kim Tae-hyun joins the team on a permanent transfer|language=Japanese|website=www.sagan-tosu.net}}</ref>

In January 2025, it was announced that Kim would be joining [[J1 League]] club [[Kashima Antlers]] following a single season at [[Sagan Tosu]].<ref>{{cite web |title=キム テヒョン選手 完全移籍加入のお知らせ {{!}} 鹿島アントラーズ オフィシャルサイト |url=https://www.antlers.co.jp/news/article/20250104-1-zrynb.html |website=鹿島アントラーズ オフィシャルサイト {{!}} KASHIMA ANTLERS |access-date=4 January 2025 |language=ja}}</ref>

